cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of learning model parameters when a fraction of the training samples are corrupted. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), cryptography (cs.CR), and neural networks (cs.NE). Given that the paper proposes a generic framework that can be applied to different types of models and corruption scenarios, it is likely to be relevant to researchers in all of these sub-fields. However, given that the paper focuses on image classifiers and generative adversarial networks, it is most likely to be classified under cs.LG and cs.CV.
